“We hear complaints more often than ever.”
This is the first warning of this kind announced by the organization to the U.S. state.
The Group referred to incidents such as the racial humiliation of black students at Missouri University and the death of 20-year-old Tori Sanders, a black man from Tennessee.
Sanders died under suspicious circumstances earlier this year after he ran out of gas on a state trip, and Missouri State Police arrested him without charge of a crime.
The warning also mentions a recent report by the Attorney General of Missouri State, according to which the probability of being stopped on the road for black drivers is 75 per cent higher than for white drivers.
