According to the latest FBI hate crime report, there were 100 hate crimes reported in Missouri in 2015, making the state the sixteenth State in terms of the number of such violations.
A travel warning is also a response to the new Missouri State Act, which will make it more difficult to bring legal action against a legal person for housing or labour discrimination.
Previously, the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) had issued warnings to travelers in Texas and Arizona after these states had enacted new immigration control laws requiring local law enforcement agencies to arrest people for immigration violations, which ACLU believed should have increased the number of racial checks.
