“No one decides to walk around the village after 5:00 p.m.”, she says.
This is a rare opportunity to look at daily life in the highlands of Papua, the former Dutch colony, which was joined to Indonesia in 1969 after a questionable referendum, when only 1,026 elders were forced to vote in public to raise their hands before the occupying forces.
