According to Human Rights Watch, five young protesters were killed and far more wounded.
The news about the murders only got to Jakarta the next day.
Three weeks later, Jokovi spoke in Jayapur, expressing condolences to the families of the victims and vowing to address the historical abuse of power in Papua.
“I want this situation to be settled immediately, never again in the future”, he said.
In October 2016, the Minister for Security, Viranto, said that he would establish a non-judicial organization to put an end to historical violations of human rights.
