The Deiyai Parliament demanded that officers involved in the incident be called to account and that the mobile police brigade be withdrawn from the region.
Paniai has always been a sick place for the Indonesian government.
The lack of meaningful development is a source of dissatisfaction among the Mee, Moni, Dani and Damal tribes scattered throughout the green central highlands of Papua.
