In the other corner of the room, Tyrone Brooks, who remembers his work as a human rights defender, took the spotlight.
He says he's already started planning next year's show.
"The performance inspires us because it not only describes the horror of what we've been through, but also teaches us," he says.
"Because if you don't learn from this lesson, it can happen again.
