Using a computer software analysis of DNA obtained from Manning and using it to create three-dimensional portraits of individuals who could have had such a genome, Dewey Harborg created a profound, though difficult, observable manifesto about not only the plasticity of DNA data - different ways of interpreting them and the inherent determinization of these interpretations - but also the notion of identity.
Manning, who was born in Bradley Edward's name, but who, as a teenager, openly claimed to be a woman, was sentenced to 20 episodes in 2013, including six violations of the Spy Act, computer fraud, and theft.
