In response to the fundamental question that arises in the slightest or nearest disruption or conflict in the banking sector, investors are not at risk; rather, the reliability of the banking system will improve.
He leads Russia, Anatoly Axakov, who is known to be sensitive to the interests of banks and their clients, a high-level professional who is highly valued at the Central Bank: virtually all the CB leadership is present at the annual activities of the association, and all significant legislative initiatives of the regulator are carried out through expert assessments of the “regions”.
