There will be two new territories in Russia that are ahead of socio-economic development: Abaza and Novotroitzk.
The relevant decisions of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, 4 August.
The boundaries and economic activities of the SAR have been defined in the territory of the city of Abaz in the Republic of Haqasiyah.
In a city of 15,000 people, there will be a special legal regime for entrepreneurship, as well as a minimum capital investment of residents and a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
This is expected to attract about 2.5 billion roubles of investment into the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of economic activities in which ABAZ has a special legal regime for business activities, such as crop production, livestock production, food production, non-alcoholic beverages and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements for the implementation of eight investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the Territory's dependence on the Abakan Mining Company.
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Hakasia had met all the conditions of the Mino-Economy for the establishment of the TOR.
The authorities of the Orenburg region have also done the same.
There, the city of Novotrojc will also establish an area ahead of economic and social development.
This will allow the monotown economy to diversify, reduce its dependence on the AO "Ural Steel" mall, and create more than 2,300 jobs and attract more than 8 billion roubles of investment.
The list of economic activities in which the new TOR will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, inter alia, freshwater fish farming, the production of feeds, medicines and medical supplies.
Novotrowitzk was the first monocities in the Orenburg oblast to become TOR.
Recall that the Territory is an economic zone with favourable tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges that is created to attract investment in improving the lives of the population.
The following are among the benefits for residents: a profit tax of no more than 5 per cent for the first five years and not less than 10 per cent for the next five years; social contributions of 7.6 per cent for 10 years; the use of the free customs zone; the preferential treatment of connections to various infrastructure facilities; and preferential rent rates.
